ENTRY            A0722   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0722001   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 12         40
TITLE      Coulomb breakup of 23O
AUTHOR     (C.Nociforo, K.L.Jones, L.H.Khiem, P.Adrich, T.Aumann,
           B.V.Carlson, D.Cortina-Gil, U.Datta Pramanik,Th.W.Elze,
           H.Emling, H.Geissel, M.Hellstroem, J.V.Kratz,
           R.Kulessa, T.Lange, Y.Leifels, H.Lenske, E.Lubkiewicz,
           G.Muenzenberg, R.Palit, H.Scheit, H.Simon, K.Suemmerer,
           S.Typel, E.Wajda, W.Walus, H.Weick,
           LAND-FRS Collaboration)
INSTITUTE  (2GERMNZ,2GERGSI,3POLUJK,3BZLITA,2SPNSAU,2GERFRK,
           2GERJLU,2GERMPH,2GERTHD)
REFERENCE  (J,PL/B,605,79,2005)
REL-REF    (I,O1715001,R.Palit+,J,PR/C,68,034318,2003)
           Details of experiment
FACILITY   (SYNCH,2GERGSI) Synchrotron with fragment separator
INC-SOURCE The 23O beam with a kinetic energy of 422 MeV/nucleon
           was produced via fragmentation reactions of a primary
           Ar-40 beam (500 MeV/nucleon) from the SIS synchrotron
           at GSI, Darmstadt. A beryllium production target,
            4 g/cm2 was used at the entrance of the fragment
           separator-FRS.
METHOD     (COINC) O-22 fragments, neutrons and gamma rays have
            been detected in coincidence.
           (EXTB,TOF,ASEP)
DETECTOR   (SCIN) Organic scintillators
           (PS) Position-sensitive silicon diode detectors (PSD)
           The neutron were detected in the LAND neutron detector.
           (CSICR) The detector has a cylindrical shape (length
            30 cm) with inner and outer diameters of 9.7 cm and
            38.3 cm, respectively, enclosing the beam pipe. The
           cylinder is subdivided into 12 azimuthal and 12 polar
           angle sectors covered by 144 individual crystals built
           from CsI(Na) scintillation material. Each crystal
           was equipped with one photomultiplier tube for light
           readout.
STATUS     (TABLE,,C.Nociforo+,J,PL/B,605,79,2005) Table 1
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
HISTORY    (20100326C) S.B.
           (20110825A) "LAND-FRS Collaboration" as 1st author was
           added, according to M.Bossant comment-SB
           (20260205U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              40
